		<hr size="1">yes, sorry should not have said sk were easy but it's right I only met some easy one's <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle><BR>But well my tactic is simple, I never fight without my pet. Pet is there, I fight, no pet I run (with some variants depending of the level of my ennemy <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle> )<BR>If you succeed to ca a fear on my pet, won't wait for it to come back, I'll whether run on its side or hit "go away" and summon a new one, specially now that I'm a 40k twink <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle><BR>Basically doing so, I killed the 4 sk I did meet so far around EC, it's right none of them had their HT up. But against anyone trying to root/snare/mez/fear etc... your pet, summoning a new one is possible during the fight, as well as the proc and doing so will perhaps make you use your mana but 1) you do not really need it in PvP anyway and 2) it will force the ennemy to use some more mana on your pet again and this will be less damage on you.</P><P>When things turn bad, just play as a necro, run around your pet and try to live long enough for the pet to kill your ennemy, the pet will show you who is the real warder <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>Fiavy the Beastlord <BR>always grouped with Flavy the drood<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
